headline: Why The Narrative Around JFrog Is Shifting After Fresh Cloud And Security Upside
summary: JFrog’s stock narrative is shifting as fresh Street research nudges its price target higher, even while fair value stays anchored near $69.22 per share and long term revenue growth assumptions remain close to 16.69%. The modest uptick in the discount rate to about 8.44% reflects a slightly higher required return on equity, but bullish analysts still see accelerating cloud and security momentum as enough to support higher target ranges in the $60 to $70 band. headline: How Recent Moves in AI and Earnings Are Rewriting the Story for Walmart
summary: Walmart’s updated stock narrative now embeds a slightly higher fair value estimate of about $119, up from roughly $118, as analysts lean into a more constructive long term outlook. Small tweaks to the model, including a marginally lower discount rate near 6.99% and a modestly higher revenue growth assumption around 4.92%, reflect growing conviction in resilient comps, expanding alternative profit streams, and early upside from agentic commerce initiatives.
